ocker` | PR | PR updates allowed Docker images used by tests. |\ndocs/functional-spec.md:232:- **Declared Docker images.** Tests that use Docker must declare every image they need in `required-docker-images.txt`. Each image must already appear in `tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>`. Tests fail otherwise.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:240:- **Docker isolation.** Docker images used in tests are pre-pulled from `allowed-docker-images`, after which the runner disables Docker networking for deterministic, isolated test runs.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:244:- **Docker tag sync.** Dependabot updates to `allowed-docker-images` trigger `sync-docker-tags.yml`, which back-commits the synchronized tags into the Dependabot PR.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:259:- **Determinism.** Tests must be reproducible. Network-dependent tests are not allowed except where they declare an `allowed-docker-image` and run against that pre-pulled image with networking disabled.\ndocs/tck.md:103:| `checkAllowedDockerImages` | Scan allowed images for vulnerabilities with grype, either all images or only those changed between two commits (§CI-scan-docker-images). |\ntests/src/org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.neo4j.driver:neo4j-java-driver:5.28.5\ntests/src/org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/gradle.properties:6:metadata.dir = org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/\ntests/src/org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/build.gradle:14:    testImplementation \"org.neo4j.driver:neo4j-java-driver:$libraryVersion\"\ntests/src/org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/user-code-filter.json:7:      \"includeClasses\" : \"org.neo4j.driver.**\"\ntests/src/org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/user-code-filter.json:10:      \"includeClasses\" : \"org_neo4j_driver.neo4j_java_driver.**\"\ntests/src/org.neo4j.driver/neo4j-java-driver/5.28.5/settings.gradle:20:rootProject.name = 'org.neo4j.driver.neo4j-j